      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mixing ibuprofen and aspirin in large doses can be dangerous and increase the risk of serious side effects, including gastrointestinal bleeding and kidney damage. It's crucial to stick to the recommended dosages: 400mg of ibuprofen three to four times a day, not exceeding 1200mg in 24 hours, and 650mg of aspirin once a day. If your pain persists, consult a healthcare professional immediately. Self-medicating with excessive doses can lead to severe complications.",
